y=Asin⁡(Bx+C)+D{\displaystyle y=A\sin(Bx+C)+D}
Find your values of A, B, C, and D.
Note that in the basic equation for sine, A = 1, B = 1, C = 0, and D = 0.

{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/8\/85\/Sinx_amplitude_change.gif","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/8\/85\/Sinx_amplitude_change.gif\/300px-Sinx_amplitude_change.gif","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":460,"bigWidth":"300","bigHeight":"300","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}
Amplitude=A{\displaystyle {\text{Amplitude}}=A}
Multiply the y-values you have by A, and graph these new points. If A is negative, the graph will flip over the x-axis. This is called a reflection.

{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/1\/1c\/Sinx_phase_change.gif","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/1\/1c\/Sinx_phase_change.gif\/300px-Sinx_phase_change.gif","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":460,"bigWidth":"300","bigHeight":"300","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}
Phase shift=CB{\displaystyle {\text{Phase shift}}={\frac {C}{B}}}
This will move the graph to the left or right. For each x-value in the period, move the x-value to the left by C/B if C/B is negative, or move each x-value to the right by C/B if C/B is positive.

{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/f\/f2\/Sinx_intercept_change.gif","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/f\/f2\/Sinx_intercept_change.gif\/300px-Sinx_intercept_change.gif","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":460,"bigWidth":"300","bigHeight":"300","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}
Vertical shift=D{\displaystyle {\text{Vertical shift}}=D}
For each y-value, move the y-value up by D if D is positive, or move the y-value down if D is negative.

